Osogbo â€” Labour unions in Osun State yesterday declared a total strike to press home their demand for payment of full salaries. The state chairman of the Nigerian Labour congress (NLC), Comrade Jacob Adekomi, said the strike will begin on Wednesday, December 27. Comrade Adekomi maintained that the government has no reason to continue paying modulated salaries to workers. He noted that efforts are on to ensure that the industrial action is effective.